# Git attributes for a personal-knowledge-system (consumer) repo.
# Seeded from the KAG skills engine so a newly bootstrapped consumer repo
# inherits append-only-ledger union where its stores actually live (the engine
# repo's .gitattributes does not reach into a consumer checkout). See the engine
# strategy doc skill-building/strategy/2026-06-09-collision-prevention-generalization.md.

# Normalize line endings.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Append-only ledger union (git built-in; no per-clone registration).
# Union keeps both sides' appended lines instead of conflicting under concurrent
# capture across worktrees. Known limit: union does not dedup or reorder;
# consumers dedup by SHA on read.
knowledge-base/commit-log.jsonl merge=union

# NOTE (deferred, deliberate): per-store union for the append-only-with-
# supersession stores (synthesis-store, evidence-store, and the like) is NOT
# enabled here yet. It must be verified store-by-store first, because the
# mutable-with-audit-trail stores (projects-store / PRJ-, taxonomy-items-store /
# ITM-, print-design-store / PRD-) edit records in place and MUST NOT be unioned
# (union would keep two divergent versions of the same record). A blanket
# *-store.jsonl rule would wrongly catch those three. Enumerate the verified
# append-only stores in a later pass rather than blanket-matching.
